  "content": {
    "intro": "The 10-complement (also called \"friends of 10\") is essential for multi-digit arithmetic. While the 5-complement works within one column, the 10-complement moves values between columns.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "What is the 10-Complement?"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "The 10-complement pairs numbers that add up to 10:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "1 and 9 (1 + 9 = 10)",
          "2 and 8 (2 + 8 = 10)",
          "3 and 7 (3 + 7 = 10)",
          "4 and 6 (4 + 6 = 10)",
          "5 and 5 (5 + 5 = 10)",
          "6 and 4 (6 + 4 = 10)",
          "7 and 3 (7 + 3 = 10)",
          "8 and 2 (8 + 2 = 10)",
          "9 and 1 (9 + 1 = 10)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Adding with 10-Complement (Carrying)"
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "style": "info",
        "text": "When adding would exceed 9: ADD 1 to the tens column, SUBTRACT the complement from ones."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Example: 8 + 5"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Set 8 (upper bead + 3 lower beads)",
          "Add 5... but 8 + 5 = 13, exceeds 9!",
          "Complement of 5 is 5",
          "Add 1 to tens column, subtract 5 from ones: 8 - 5 = 3",
          "Result: 13 (1 in tens, 3 in ones) ✓"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Addition Examples"
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "headers": [
          "Problem",
          "Complement",
