    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Do I need to teach 5-complement before 10-complement?",
        "answer": "Usually yes, because 5-complement is simpler and used within problems that also need 10-complement. But some curricula teach them together."
      },
      {
        "question": "This seems complicated. Will my child really learn this?",
        "answer": "Yes! Kids learn these patterns faster than adults because they haven't solidified other calculation methods yet. Trust the process."
      },
      {
        "question": "How long until complements become automatic?",
        "answer": "With 15-20 minutes of daily practice, most kids internalize the main patterns within 2-3 months. Full automaticity takes longer."
      }
